chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if your obsessive compulsive disorder affects your driving.
chunks.plain_content:
Obsessive compulsive disorder and driving
You must tell DVLA if your obsessive compulsive disorder affects your driving.

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:
Obsessive compulsive disorder and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.

chunks.html_content:
Ask your doctor if you’re not sure if your obsessive compulsive disorder will affect your driving.

Fill in the M1 questionnaire and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
